definition.value: A 2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucoside having an inosityl group attached at the 1-position.
A 2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucoside having an L-cysteinylamino group at the 2-position and an inosityl group attached at the 1-position.
A bridged compound that is cyclohexane with a methylene bridge between carbons 1 and 4 and a double bond at position 2.
A chemical substance that encourages a cell to commence cell division, triggering mitosis.
A cyanine dye comprising the thiazole orange cation [1-methyl-4-[(3-methyl-1,3-benzothiazol-2(3H)-ylidene)methyl]quinolinium] with the p-tosylate counterion.

An organic chloride salt composed of 3,7-diaminophenothiazin-5-ium and chloride ions in a 1:1 ratio. A strongly metachromatic dye, useful for the staining of acid mucopolysaccharides. It is also a common nuclear stain and can be used for the demonstration of Nissl substance in nerve cells of the CNS.
A C1 cyanine dye having benzothiazolium-2-yl and quinolinium-4-yl substituents.
An unsymmetrical C3 cyanine dye having benzothiazolium-2-yl and quinolinium-4-yl substituents.
An EC 2.1.1.* (methyltransferases) inhibitor that interferes with the action of sterol methyltransferase.
A xanthene dye that is fluorescein bearing two fluoro substituents at positions 2' and 7'.
A tetramethylrhodium dye conjugated to the bicyclic peptide phalloidin via a thiourea linkage.
A sterol ester obtained by formal condensation of the 3-hydroxy group of ergosterol with the carboxy group of any carboxylic acid.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA in which the 3-hydroxy fatty acyl group is specified as 3-hydroxyicosanoyl.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA in which the 3-hydroxy fatty acyl group is specified as 3-hydroxydocosanoyl.
A very long-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-hydroxytetracosanoic acid.
A 3-oxoacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxoicosanoic acid.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA obtained from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxodocosanoic acid.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 3-oxotetracosanoic acid.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol in which the acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as oleoyl.
An organic chloride salt having N-[9-(2-carboxyphenyl)-6-(diethylamino)-3H-xanthen-3-ylidene]-N-ethylethanaminium as the counterion. An amphoteric dye commonly used as a fluorochrome.
